Hereâ€™s a quick guide on how to run Jupyter Notebook (.ipynb) files directly from GitHub using various platforms:

USING GOOGLE COLAB:
1. Open Google Colab
2. Open Notebook from GitHub:
    Click on the "GitHub" tab in the "Open a notebook" dialog.
    Enter your GitHub repository URL or search for the notebook.
    Select the notebook you want to run.
3. Add a Colab Badge to Your README:
    You can add a badge in your README.md file for direct access.
[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/yourusername/repository-name/blob/main/path_to_your_notebook.ipynb)
